title: Average weekly working hours in Sweden 2019 , by type of employment
yAxis: Average number of working hours per week
summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is appeared to be the highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
There is a difference of 9.9 between the maximum Form of Employment Self-employed and minimum Form of Employment Temporary employed.
min_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
mid_summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is appeared to be the highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.

max_summary: This is a bar chart representing Form of Employment in the x axis and Average number of working hours per week in the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is appeared to be the highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
Second maximum Average number of working hours per week is found at Form of Employment Permanently employed.
The maximum Form of Employment Self-employed has got 1.39 times higher Average number of working hours per week than the minimum Form of Employment Temporary employed.
Average number of working hours per week at Form of Employment Self-employed is 35.4 , second place is Permanently employed at 30.4, and thirdly is Employed total at 30.2.
The Form of Employment Self-employed has 1.17 times more Average number of working hours per week than average.
The Average number of working hours per week is 121.5 if we add up values of all Form of Employments.
